claims:
1. A prelithiation process for lithium metal negative electrode protection, comprising the steps of:
      (1) coating the surface of a current collector to form an organic polymer film; the coating thickness of the organic polymer film is 5-200 mu m;
      (2) assembling the current collector coated with the organic polymer film, a lithium sheet, a diaphragm and electrolyte into a battery for discharge treatment, and depositing metal lithium on the surface of the current collector;
      (3) taking out the current collector with the surface deposited with the metal lithium obtained in the step (2), and obtaining the negative electrode material which has a protective film on the surface and can be used for a lithium metal battery;
      in the step (1), the organic polymer adopted by the organic polymer film is one or more of oxidized polyacrylonitrile, vulcanized polyacrylonitrile, seleno-polyacrylonitrile, telluride polyacrylonitrile, selenium-doped vulcanized polyacrylonitrile, tellurium-doped vulcanized polyacrylonitrile and selenium-tellurium-doped vulcanized polyacrylonitrile;
      the current collector is made of one or more of copper foil, gold foil and silver foil;
      in the step (2), a small amount of non-metal atoms in the organic polymer can react with metal lithium to generate an inorganic lithiation compound, and a protective film is formed in situ;
      the organic polymer film also comprises an adhesive, wherein the adhesive is one or more of polyvinylidene fluoride, styrene butadiene rubber, carboxymethyl cellulose, acrylonitrile multipolymer and polytetrafluoroethylene;
      in the organic polymer film, the mass ratio of the organic polymer to the adhesive is 10: 1-1: 1;
      for the negative electrode material obtained in the step (3), on one hand, the organic polymer can guide lithium ions to be uniformly deposited in the charging and discharging process, so that the generation of lithium dendrites is inhibited, on the other hand, a small amount of active non-metal atoms in the organic polymer can react with metal lithium in the discharging process to generate inorganic lithiation, a protective film is formed in situ, the metal lithium is prevented from reacting with electrolyte to generate dead lithium, the consumption of lithium is reduced, and the cycle performance and the capacity retention rate of the metal lithium are improved.
